==English==
===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אהרן|אַהֲרֹן]] ''(Ahărōn)'' = 'air, vanity'.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-proper noun}}

# A male [[given name]].
# A person in the [[Old Testament]], the elder brother of [[Moses]] in the Book of the [[Exodus]].

